column2: Sunny- cold - after several days of cold- rainy days.
Hazy- breezy morning. Loons- eagles and ducks present on lake. Day after the Memorial Day Holiday-the lake saw moderate activity over the weekend most of which were fishermen and pleasure boating.

90 deg day- sunny- humid. Very nice on the water. Blue skies- breezy. There is an abundance of coontail on the lake making the lake look a bit less appealing. There was quite a bit of boating and swimming being done on the weekend of 6/23 + 24.

Beautiful- cloudless morning with a breeze. Little Bearskin Lake is getting lower due to the lack of rain. The aquatic plants are thick at the surface making it difficult to boat and use beaches in the bays. The abundance of aquatic plants make swimming relatively unpleasant.
The weather was beautiful. Sunny- calm and no wind. The water was like glass. The lake was beautiful.
Bright sunny day. Water a brown stain color more then usual.
Beautiful clear day. Lots of rain over the past weeks. Flushing nutrients from swamp- plants thriving.
Water high- weeds up making boating difficult. Water appears to have a greenish color. Still very warm with less rain.
Bright-sunny day with a light wind. Water clear except for a moderate amount of slimmy algae on the surface.
